      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should absolutely avoid taking ibuprofen with lithium, as it can dangerously increase lithium levels in your blood and cause severe toxicity.\nInstead, try taking your lithium with a small snack and plenty of water to help settle your stomach.\nIf the nausea persists, you should contact your doctor immediately to discuss safe alternatives, but please do not self-medicate with ibuprofen.",
